{
  "text": "The Pima Indians of Arizona are examined every $ 2 y as part of a continuing longitudinal epidemiological study of NIDDM. [CITATION_1] Brie\u00afy, these examinations include a medical history and tests relating to diabetes and other major health problems. Forty healthy, full-blooded USA Pima Indians who attended a biennial exam between June 1994 and September 1996 were recruited to match the sex and age ( AE 2 y) of the 40 Pimas studied in Mexico.",
  "citation_candidates": [
